Becoming your mama is the best thing to ever happen to me I don’t feel like I started actually living my life fully until you were born. 

Today marks year 26 that I lost both my parents in the same year. 

The last memory I have of my mother was her tucking me in bed and telling me goodnight I remember that night as if it were yesterday it was a cold rainy night mid October in Chicago I couldn’t sleep well that night because of the storm my mom never returned that night earlier in the same year I lost my father he passed away In San Francisco he also went out one night and never returned. 

As I get older and step into myself more and more I find myself feeling more comfortable talking about my angels as I know they would want me to celebrate them rather than be sad.

I share something so close to my heart and feel called to share my story and be vulnerable more now than ever because maybe this will help someone else going through something similar just know your not alone your angels are still with you and they are proud that you chose to keep going even when it felt impossible hold onto the people you love and tell them you love them. 

Love those who love you.
And be kind.
Light and Love.
